<p>I'm struggling with native <a href="http://plugins.telerik.com/cordova/plugin/native-page-transitions" rel="nofollow">Page Transitions plugin</a>, because the old view remains in transition then renders the new view i'm transiting to.</p>  <p>I've figured out that this was because the plugin waits the new view to be rendered to actually display it.</p>  <p>This being said, my new view makes a restangular request to the server and that's the cause (I belive).</p>  <p>So what I want to do is to display a loading icon, and after the transition, to execute my controller's logic.</p>  <p>I thought that promises would do the thing but they were not.</p>  <p>Some relevant code :</p>  <p><strong>Services.js</strong> </p>  <pre><code>angular.module('starter.services', []) .factory('ListPosts', function(Restangular) {     return {         getPosts: function(catId){             return Restangular.one('api/v1/list-posts-category/', catId).getList().$object;         },         refreshPosts : function(catId){             return Restangular.one('api/v1/list-posts-category/', catId).withHttpConfig({                 cache: false             }).getList();         }     } }) </code></pre>  <p><strong>Controllers.js</strong></p>  <pre><code>...     .controller('CatPostsCtrl', function($scope, $stateParams, $state, Restangular, $ionicHistory, localStorageService, ListPosts) {         $scope.posts = ListPosts.getPosts($stateParams.CategoryId);}) </code></pre>  <p>With this code, the transition is not as I want it to be , I still see the old view while transiting. </p>